link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
mathematica: t = PositionIndex[FactorInteger[#][[1, 1]] & /@ Range[10^6]]; f[n_] := Times @@ Power[If[# == 1, 1, NextPrime@ #] & /@ First@ #, Last@ #] &@ Transpose@ FactorInteger@ n; Flatten@ Map[Position[Lookup[t, FactorInteger[#][[1, 1]]], #] &[f@ f[2 #]] &, Map[Times @@ Power[If[# == 1, 1, NextPrime[#, -1]] & /@ First@#, Last@#] &@ Transpose@ FactorInteger[2 # - 1] &, Floor[#/2] + # & /@ Range@ 80]] (* _Michael De Vlieger_, Aug 07 2016, Version 10 *)
xref: Cf. also A273669 (natural numbers not in this sequence).
